diff --git a/docs/api/structures/shared-allocator-options.md b/docs/api/structures/shared-allocator-options.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..58925ea1b2
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/shared-allocator-options.md
@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+# SharedAllocatorOptions Object
+
+* `arrayBuffer` boolean (optional) - Whether `new ArrayBuffer(size)` allocations
+  should use the shared memory pool. Default is `true`.
+* `typedArrays` boolean (optional) - Whether length-based typed-array
+  allocations such as `new Uint8Array(length)` should use the shared memory
+  pool. Default is `true`.
+* `arrayLike` boolean (optional) - Whether array-like typed-array constructor
+  inputs such as `new Uint8Array([1, 2, 3])` should use the shared memory pool.
+  Default is `false`.
+* `maxAllocationSize` number (optional) - Overrides the pool's per-allocation
+  limit for this allocator scope.
+* `onOverflow` string (optional) - Controls what happens when the pool cannot
+  satisfy an allocation. Can be `fallback` or `throw`. Default is `fallback`,
+  or `throw` when `channel` is provided.
+* `channel` [SharedMemoryChannel](../shared-memory.md#class-sharedmemorychannel)
+  (optional) - Affines shared-backed buffers and views allocated by this scope
+  to the channel. Electron pre-registers their payload id and uses
+  channel-private fast-path metadata on the exact allocated object for later
+  `channel.send(data[, tag])` calls. This is the recommended mode for bursty
+  channel producers because repeated sends can use the channel's internal
+  coalesced wakeup path. Channel-affined allocations use reusable bucket-sized
+  backing blocks internally, so variable-size payloads can reuse released shared
+  blocks while preserving the requested JavaScript byte length. When the channel
+  enables its preallocated allocator, matching allocations can also reuse
+  shared-backed slots prepared at channel creation time. Temporary shared-backed
+  allocations that are not reachable from the callback return value are returned
+  to the channel allocator when the scope exits. The channel must use the same
+  `SharedMemoryPool`.
