diff --git a/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-message.md b/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-message.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..d5d2a5ee23
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-message.md
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+# SharedMemoryChannelMessage Object
+
+* `event` Event - Original IPC event.
+* `data` ArrayBuffer - Shared-backed payload bytes.
+* `tag` number | null - Numeric tag supplied by the sender.
+* `view` Function\<ArrayBufferView\> - Returns a typed view over `data`. The
+  first call creates the view lazily and later calls return the same view.
+* `released` boolean - Whether `release()` has been called.
+* `retained` boolean - Whether `retain()` has been called.
+* `release` Function\<boolean\> - Releases local tracking for the payload. For
+  shared-backed channel payloads, this also lets the sender detach borrowed
+  sender-side objects if needed and reuse the shared block. In
+  `delivery: 'latest'` channels, release does not make the sender-owned slot an
+  immutable snapshot; the sender may overwrite it for later messages.
+* `retain` Function\<[SharedMemoryChannelLease](shared-memory-channel-lease.md)\> -
+  Prevents automatic local release after the handler returns and returns a lease
+  with `release()`.
diff --git a/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-options.md b/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-options.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..954d4a613c
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/shared-memory-channel-options.md
@@ -0,0 +1,65 @@
+# SharedMemoryChannelOptions Object
+
+* `name` string - Logical channel name used to match sender and receiver
+  endpoints.
+* `slotSize` number (optional) - Fixed copy-fallback payload slot size in bytes.
+  Default is `65536` when `copyFallback` is `allow`. Ignored when `classes` is
+  specified.
+* `slotCount` number (optional) - Number of fixed-size copy-fallback slots.
+  Default is `256` when `copyFallback` is `allow`. Ignored when `classes` is
+  specified.
+* `classes` [SharedMemorySlotClass[]](shared-memory-slot-class.md) (optional) -
+  Size classes for variable-size copy-fallback payloads. The smallest class that
+  can contain a payload is used.
+* `views` Record\<number, Function\> (optional) - Numeric tag to typed-array or
+  `DataView` constructor map used by `SharedMemoryChannel` message `view()`.
+  When omitted, `view()` returns a `Uint8Array`. When supplied, messages must
+  use a registered numeric tag.
+* `maxTagSize` number (optional) - Maximum encoded tag metadata length for
+  copy-fallback rings. Default is `1024`.
+* `overflow` string (optional) - Controls what happens when a ring has no free
+  slot. Can be `drop-oldest`, `drop-newest`, or `throw`. Default is
+  `drop-oldest`.
+* `oversized` string (optional) - Controls what happens when a payload is larger
+  than every configured class. Can be `allocate`, `drop`, or `throw`. Default is
+  `allocate`.
+* `oversizedSlotCount` number (optional) - Number of slots in dynamically
+  allocated oversized rings. Default is `2`.
+* `copyFallback` string (optional) - Controls what happens when `send` receives
+  data that is not shared-backed by the channel pool. Can be `throw` or `allow`.
+  Default is `throw`.
+* `ownership` string (optional) - Controls shared-backed payload ownership for
+  `send`. Can be `transfer` or `borrow`. Default is `transfer`.
+* `delivery` string (optional) - Controls whether repeated sends of the same
+  shared-backed payload are delivered as a safe snapshot or as the latest
+  sender-owned bytes. Can be `snapshot` or `latest`. Default is `snapshot`.
+  `latest` defaults `ownership` to `borrow` and rejects `ownership: 'transfer'`.
+* `allocator` boolean | string | Object (optional) - Enables a preallocated
+  channel allocator for `SharedMemory.withAllocator(..., { channel })`. Can be
+  `true`, `auto`, or an object. The allocator currently requires
+  `delivery: 'latest'`. When enabled, length-based `Uint8Array` and
+  `ArrayBuffer` allocations first try to reuse preallocated shared-backed slots
+  before falling back to dynamic shared allocation.
+  * `preset` string (optional) - Allocator preset. Currently only `auto` is
+    supported.
+  * `classes` Object[] (optional) - Preallocated slot classes. Each entry has:
+    * `size` number - Slot capacity in bytes.
+    * `count` number - Number of slots to preallocate for that capacity.
+  * `overflow` string (optional) - Behavior when no preallocated slot can be
+    used. Can be `allocate` or `throw`. Default is `allocate`.
+  * `classFallback` string (optional) - Behavior when the smallest matching
+    class is full. Can be `larger`, `allocate`, or `throw`. Default is
+    `larger`.
+
+When `copyFallback` is `throw` and no `slotSize`, `slotCount`, or `classes` are
+provided, `createChannel` does not allocate ring storage. This is the preferred
+mode for zero-copy shared-backed payloads.
+
+With `delivery: 'latest'`, the sender may send the same shared-backed payload
+again before the receiver releases the previous message. The receiver may
+observe bytes written after `send()` returned. Use this only for latest-value
+streams where overwritten in-flight payloads are acceptable.
+
+When `allocator` is enabled with `delivery: 'latest'`, `send()` makes the sent
+slot reusable by later allocator scopes. The sender must not treat the old
+object as an immutable snapshot after `send()` succeeds.
